<title>POLAND: POLISH BANK SECTOR CLIMATE INDEX FLAT IN APRIL.</title>
<headline>POLISH BANK SECTOR CLIMATE INDEX FLAT IN APRIL.</headline>
<dateline>WARSAW 1997-04-16</dateline>
<text>
<p>Poland's banking climate index held nearly unchanged in April, easing 0.5 point to 49.3, a poll released on Wednesday by the private Pentor institute showed.</p>
<p>The monthly survey showed the index called &quot;Pengab&quot; dipped slightly due to lower bank evaluations of foreign currency credit and deposits.</p>
<p>The index, based on a scale of minus 100 to plus 100, polled 204 bank managers and is commissioned monthly by the Polish Banking Association (ZBP).</p>
<p>-- Warsaw Newsroom +48 22 653 9700</p>
